.DT
appoint_position
Disk World creator help
appoint_position

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
appoint_position -  Dummy function for guilds without positions This method appoints the player to a position.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int appoint_position(string sub_guild,
string position,
string player_name)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^sub_guild%^RESET%^ - the sub guild
%^BOLD%^position%^RESET%^ - the position
%^BOLD%^player_name%^RESET%^ - the player
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
POSITION_FAIL if it failed, POSITION_OK if it succeeded.
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/guilds/standard.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

Dummy function for guilds without positions
This method appoints the player to a position.   If sub_guild is 0,
the guild object is supposed to figure out the subguild from the 
player_name.
.EP

